Text.Value: Using Source Finder Mode:
• Ensure the unit is in the Rate mode.
• Depress and hold the RATE button until a "1" is visible on the display.
• The unit is now in the Source Finder Mode
• To exit Source Finder Mode:
• The unit is now in the Normal Rate Mode
• Press and hold the RATE button until a "0" appears on the display.
• Release the RATE button
• Release the RATE button.

The AN/UDR-14 Radiacmeter has a mode in which the operator can "hear" the occurrence of the GM detector registering a gamma radiation count. This allows the user to leave the unit in this mode and simply listen (rather than having to watch the display) to "GM tube count rate" as an indication of the intensity of the radiation field.

The more rapid the count rate (sound), the greater the field intensity. This method of operation is also useful when trying to find the source of gamma radiation. You can simply move in the direction of increasing "GM tube count rate" as indicated by the sound produced by the instrument.

Employment

Using Source Finder Mode

  • To use Source Finder, the unit should be in Rate mode.
  • Depress and hold the RATE button until a "1" is visible on the display and then release the RATE button.
  • The unit is now in the Source Finder Mode.
  • To exit the Source Finder Mode and return to normal RATE mode
  • Press and hold the RATE button until a "0" appears on the display and then release the RATE button.
  • This will put the unit back into the normal RATE mode.
